SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYMonday 31 January S10 V1 Lionel Messi could start for Paris St Germain as they host on Nice in the French Cup on Monday in a clash which is, ironically, between the two clubs at the head of the league standings. More details at www.soccer6.co.za M1 Casa Pia vs Penafiel: Casa Pia are chasing promotion and sit in second place in the Portuguese second division. Penafiel have won once in their past six games.M2 Hapoel Afula vs Hapoel Rishon LeZion: Hapoel Afula have won two successive games. Hapoel Rishon LeZion have won twice and drawn the other of their past three Israel second division games.M3 Kafr Qasim vs Hapoel Ramat HaSharon: Kafr Qasim are five poins clear at the top of the Israeli second division. Hapoel Ramat HaSharon are winless in their last four games.M4 Sektzia Nes Tziona vs Hapoel Ramat Gan: Sektzia Nes Tziona won away in their last two games against Hapoel Ramat Gan, scoring seven goals in the process.M5 Ironi Kiryat Shmona vs Bnei Sakhnin: Five of the last six games between these two clubs have been won by the away team.M6 Estoril vs Pacos Ferreira: Four of the past six meetings between these Portuguese clubs have ended in 1-1 draws. Estoril have won the other two.M7 Portsmouth vs Charlton Athletic: Portsmouth are looking to snap a four match unbeaten run. Charlton have won on their past seven trips to Fratton Park.M8 Ibiza vs Real Zaragoza (22:00)M9 Paris Saint-Germain vs Nice: The top two teams in the league have been drawn against each other in thr last-16 of the French Cup.M10 Famalicao vs Arouca: Both clubs are in the relegation zone in the Portuguese league. Famalicao have won one of their past eight matches. Arouca have not won in their last seven games. Suggested permutation:Cost: R4.001 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 2, 3 x 1 x 1